## Ranked candidates (36-byte + skin ring + fingerprint fit)

### #1 — `SoftwareBlendSkeletalShaderPrimitive` (clientSkeletalAnimation)

**Why it still ranks #1:** It is the **only** high-volume NPC skeletal path with PNCT-36 on the skin ring, typical creature LOD vertex counts in the 1k–3k range, and explicit lock/copy tail logic in-tree.

| Item | Location |
|------|----------|
| **Format (36 B)** | `dynamicFormat`: position + normal + color0 + tc sets — ```1336:1364:src/engine/client/library/clientSkeletalAnimation/src/shared/appearance/SoftwareBlendSkeletalShaderPrimitive.cpp``` |
| **Lock** | ```839:839:src/engine/client/library/clientSkeletalAnimation/src/shared/appearance/SoftwareBlendSkeletalShaderPrimitive.cpp``` — `m_dynamicStream->lock(m_vertexCount)` |
| **Write loop** | Single-stream path: skin to `m_systemStream` via `skinData()` / `fillVertexBuffer()` / `fillVertexBufferHard()` (```788:790```, ```1922+```, ```2633+```), then **memcpy copy** to dynamic: ```841:869:src/engine/client/library/clientSkeletalAnimation/src/shared/appearance/SoftwareBlendSkeletalShaderPrimitive.cpp``` |
| **“World space” note** | Positions are **model-root / appearance-local** from `transformArray[].rotateTranslate_l2p()` (```2643:2644```). O2W is set separately at ```490:491```. Centroid ≈ NPC world position in your probe likely means either (a) probe adds appearance translation, or (b) **tail bytes are stale ring data** from a prior draw that *was* world-space at `[-2816, 0, -6400]`. |
| **Ruled-out branches** | Multi-stream copy @ ```758:763``` (runtime `ms_useMultiStreamVertexBuffers=0` per ```567:567```). Hard-skin SSE fill @ ```2633:2661``` still ends in same copy path. |

**Exact tail mechanism (#1 candidate): lock count vs copy count mismatch**

The source documents this explicitly:

```842:869:src/engine/client/library/clientSkeletalAnimation/src/shared/appearance/SoftwareBlendSkeletalShaderPrimitive.cpp
// CONSULT-32 PROBE D: lock reserves m_vertexCount; copy writes systemStream count. If
// they differ, the dynamic slice tail [copyN, m_vertexCount) is NEVER written -> on the
// D3D11 skin ring that tail is uninitialized fresh-WRITE_DISCARD memory (prev generation,
// world-space) -> spike. Probe B showed the spike tail starts at firstIdx == copyN.
outIt.copy(m_systemStream->beginReadOnly(), m_systemStream->getNumberOfVertices());
```

If `lockN = m_vertexCount` (1647/2664) but `copyN = m_systemStream->getNumberOfVertices()` is smaller by ~27, indices drawing verts `[copyN .. lockN)` read **stale skin-ring memory** — classically a prior mesh’s world-space positions at `[-2816, 0, -6400]`. That produces a **contiguous tail** with a correct bulk centroid at the current NPC.

**Reconcile with your exclusions:** Path log @ ```663:680``` caps at 300 entries; Probe A/D @ ```798:831``` only fires for `ssN >= 1000`. If the spiking mesh’s prepare pass didn’t land in those buckets, SBSSP would look “absent” while still owning the buffer. Latest handoff (`.planning/handoff/2026-06-07-cape-spike-LIVE-ONLY-undefined-memory-reframe.md`) also notes: systemStream “tight” + dynamic tail garbage ⇒ **copy destination vs unlock read pointer may diverge on skin ring after discard** — a D3D11 plumbing bug, but the **writer entry point is still this prepareToDraw copy**.

**Alternate tail mechanism (if copyN == lockN):** Last ~27 verts skinned with bad/stale `transformArray[boneIndex]` (hardpoint slots never filled in `Skeleton::calculateBindPoseModelToRootTransforms()` — handoff §“CODEX-31”). Those verts get garbage `rotateTranslate_l2p()` output while the bulk is fine.

